color palette analyzer stanford vis group home papers people video stanford vis group color palette analyzer attention to color names is important for data visualization ensuring that each color can be unambiguously named makes it easier to refer to elements in conversation experimental evidence also suggests that nameable colors are better remembered here we use a color naming model to analyze color palettes the tools examines both individual saliency scores how uniquely nameable a color value is and color name distance how much the names used to describe palette colors overlap for more please see our paper custom rss stanford computer science
